# latex-paper-accuracy-review — History

## v3.1.0 (2026-04-06)

**Changed by:** Session — Fourth review pass with Opus 4.6 (1M context)
**Verification:** verified-local (pixi run paper-build, 42035 bytes, 14 files)

### What changed
- Bumped version from 3.0.0 to 3.1.0
- Added Step 0 (Consult prior review notes) to Verified Workflow
- Added 2 new error patterns: Pattern 19 (pipeline pass classification vs threshold mismatch), Pattern 20 (subtle cost rounding at third decimal place)
- Added 2 new "When to Use" triggers for late-stage rounding review and pipeline pass classification
- Added tags: BCa-bootstrap, pass-classification, rounding
- Updated Overview outcome to include v3.1.0 findings
- Added v3.1.0 session outcome to Results & Parameters
- Added "Name the method precisely" guidance in Step 2b

### Why
Fourth review pass of `docs/arxiv/haiku/paper.tex`. After 3 prior review rounds, remaining issues shifted to subtle rounding discrepancies ($0.039 vs $0.038, $0.099 vs $0.098), undisclosed pipeline pass classification mismatches (16/1080 runs), and unnamed bootstrap CI method. Consulted prior skills before starting to prevent redundant work.

